enriched_requirements.full_sentence:
An AIFI shall formulate comprehensive Board-approved policies on the Large
Exposures Framework that, inter alia, include provisions:
(1) to determine credit exposure limits of its refinancing portfolio;

(2) Where one counterparty has fully or partly guaranteed the exposure of the other
counterparty, or is liable by other means, and the exposure is so significant that the
guarantor is likely to default if a claim occurs;

(4) When the expected source of funds to repay the loans of both counterparties is the
same and neither counterparty has another independent source of income from
which the loan may be serviced and fully repaid;

(ii) Where one counterparty has fully or partly guaranteed the exposure of the other
counterparty, or is liable by other means, and the exposure is so significant that
the guarantor is likely to default if a claim occurs;

(iv) When the expected source of funds to repay the loans of both counterparties is
the same and neither counterparty has another independent source of income
from which the loan may be serviced and fully repaid;

Further, the repeal of
these directions, instructions, or guidelines shall not in any way prejudicially affect:
(1) any right, obligation or liability acquired, accrued, or incurred thereunder;
